	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />okay so I've modded a regular ntsc us nes with a rgb ppu.  Everything works great except the graphics display big vertical lines.  I've read about this issues on other forums and apparently it's very common.  I was wondering if there's any good way to remove/reduce these lines?  I would imagine it's a bit hard to find info on fixing this problem as most people probably wouldn't be bothered to add a rgb ppu to a nes
<br />
<br />Right now I'm using <a href="http://www.gamesx.com/grafx/pce_rgb.jpg" class="postlink">http://www.gamesx.com/grafx/pce_rgb.jpg</a> &lt;- this amp to brighten the dark picture.  Works great, except for the lines.
<br />
<br />The amped rgb signal goes into a rgb to s-video encoder to my tv.  This encoder works flawlessly with my snes, genesis, and arcade boards so I don't put the blame on it.

		

